items.name: Psychology Wiki
items.title: Psychology Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Psychology Wiki
items.desc:
We aim to provide an up-to-date, authoritative statement of knowledge, theory, and practice in the whole field of psychology. The site is written to serve both staff and students of our academic community, to inform professionals, both in training and in the field, and to provide information for the people we seek to help.
By using the latest collaborative editing software we have built a new kind of knowledge structure for our science that can be shaped and maintained, to the highest academic standards, by our profession as a whole.

We aim for factual accuracy and all articles should be properly referenced. We also aim to be a forum for ideas, so on each discussion page we encourage alternative opinion, proposals for hypotheses requiring verification, practitioner reports, user views, etc.

For how this might be achieved see the Psychology Wiki program of works.

items.name: Mythology Wiki
items.title: Mythology Wiki
items.headline: Mortal! Come check out Mythology Wiki!
items.desc: Mythology Wiki is a compendium of different cultures' myths, legends, and folk tales. Read about mythical creatures such as the Hydra or the nine-tailed foxes. In addition to reading about mythical creatures and myths, learn about how they are portrayed in modern-day popular culture. With all this goodness, what reason would you not have to check us out? Join today, mortal!

items.name: Astrology Wiki
items.title: Astrology Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Astrology Wiki
items.desc: At the Astrology Wikia, we hope to inform you about Astrology and the many different types of it. The wiki has Western Astrology, Chinese Astrology, Vedic Astrology, Mayan Astrology, and more! Help the wiki out by adding new pages and more information to the pages that have already been started. All who are interested in astrology are welcome on the wiki!

items.name: Googology Wiki
items.title: Googology Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Googology Wiki
items.desc: Googology Wiki is a free online encyclopedia and community dedicated to googology, the study of large numbers and their nomenclature. There are articles about numbers used on everyday life, as well as numbers far beyond human comprehension. This wiki was created to gather the rather sporadic large number community into a single place. If you are fascinated by numbers like googol and googolplex, and you want to know what a giggol, grangol or meameamealokkapoowa oompa is, why not help us out?

items.name: Dragonology Wiki
items.title: Dragonology Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to  Dragonology Wiki
items.desc: The Dragonology Wiki is an encyclopedia about the study of dragons, their many types, and dragonologists which study dragons. Anyone can contribute information to this encyclopedia. The goal of the Dragonology Wiki is to have the best resource for dragonology in the world! Enter now to learn more about dragons, the extremely rare genus of reptiles!

items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraft Archaeology Wiki
items.desc: The Minecraft Archaeology Wiki is a Wiki about the fan made Archeology mod for Minecraft. This mod adds fossil blocks, scarab tools and eventually dinosaurs to the game. This wiki helps to explain how the fossil blocks work and what the percentage chance for various drops and dinosaurs are. Please feel free to contribute!

items.name: Alien Anthology Wiki
items.title: Alien Anthology Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Alien Anthology Wiki
items.desc:
Alien Anthology Wiki is a collaborative website devoted to information about the Alien and Prometheus film series.   

Alien is a 1979 science fiction horror film.  The film's title refers to its primary antagonist: a highly aggressive extraterrestrial creature which stalks and kills the crew of a spaceship.  The popular movie spawned a number of sequels, as well as the prequel, Prometheus.

Anyone is welcome to edit the wiki and contribute their knowledge of this series of horrific sci-fi films.

items.name: Fossils and Archeology Mod Revival Wiki
items.title: Fossils and Archeology Mod Revival Wiki
items.headline: Fossils and Archeology Revival Mod Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Fossils and Archeology Revival mod Wiki! The Fossils and Archeology Revival mod (affectionately known as F/A Revival or simply Revival) is a continuation of the original Fossils and Archeology Minecraft mod created by Flammarilva. Revival provides the player with scientifically accurate prehistoric creatures to interact with and an engaging archeology experience that culminates in an encounter with an ancient boss named Anu. This mod supports both SSP (Survival Single Player) and SMP (Survival Multiplayer) using Forge in Minecraft 1.7.10. The newest version, 7.3.2, is dependent on Llibrary 1.5.0 - 1.7.10 or higher and cannot be played without it.
